# StudyNotion AI Roadmap + Course Recommendation System

We will implement a production-ready AI Roadmap + Internal Course Recommendation system. This will transform the generated roadmaps into a business growth engine by suggesting instructor-created courses directly matching the student's selected learning path.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Schema Changes:** The `suggestedCourses` field in `LearningRoadmap` will be migrated from `[ObjectId]` to `[{ course: ObjectId, relevanceScore: Number }]`. To prevent breakage of existing user roadmaps, we have designed a **live migration utility** that automatically updates old documents on startup and handles both formats gracefully in repositories.

---

## Proposed Changes

We will implement the system across 9 logical phases.

### Phase 1: Existing Course Structure Analysis (Completed)
- **Course & Category Status:** Checked schemas. Courses have `status: "Published"` or `status: "Draft"`. We will ensure only `Published` courses are queried.
- **Instructors:** Course references `instructor` (User). We will populate instructor data in queries.
- **Learning Roadmap Schema:** `LearningRoadmap.js` references courses directly. We will extend this schema.

### Phase 2: Course Matching Engine [NEW]
#### [NEW] [courseRecommendationService.js](file:///d:/Working%20Projects/Study_Notion_MERN-stack/server/services/courseRecommendationService.js)
Create a programmatic recommendation engine matching courses using:
- `courseName`, `category`, `tag`, `courseDescription`, `whatYouWillLearn`.
- **Semantic Synonym & Relation Map:** Predefine technical mappings (e.g. `React` is related to `Redux`, `Next.js`, `JavaScript`, etc.) to calculate realistic matching percentages.
- **Scoring Algorithm:**
  - Direct exact string/token matches on course name get **80% - 96%** relevance.
  - Related tech terms from mapping get **70% - 95%** relevance.
  - Category, tags, description keyword overlaps get **30% - 69%**.
- **Filters & Constraints:** Score must be `> 70%`, maximum limit of 5 courses, and courses must be `Published`.

### Phase 3: AI Prompt Upgrade
#### [MODIFY] [AIService.js](file:///d:/Working%20Projects/Study_Notion_MERN-stack/server/services/AIService.js)
- Upgrade `buildRoadmapPrompt` to incorporate matched internal course list inside the prompt context.
- Add strict, high-priority system instructions for the LLM to:
  1. Prefer StudyNotion internal courses.
  2. Recommend internal courses *before* external resources in milestones.
  3. Use the exact 24-character hexadecimal MongoDB `courseId`.
  4. Only fall back to external resources if no suitable internal course matches.
  5. Keep recommendations natural and educational.

### Phase 4: Extend Roadmap Schema
#### [MODIFY] [LearningRoadmap.js](file:///d:/Working%20Projects/Study_Notion_MERN-stack/server/models/LearningRoadmap.js)
Extend `suggestedCourses` field to include relevance score:
```javascript
suggestedCourses: [
  {
    course: {
      type: mongoose.Schema.Types.ObjectId,
      ref: "Course",
      required: true,
    },
    relevanceScore: {
      type: Number,
      required: true,
    },
  },
]
```
#### [MODIFY] [RoadmapRepository.js](file:///d:/Working%20Projects/Study_Notion_MERN-stack/server/repositories/RoadmapRepository.js)
- Update population fields to nested populate (`suggestedCourses.course` instead of `suggestedCourses`).
- Handle both old array structure and new object structure to guarantee full backward compatibility.
- Perform an asynchronous migration on server start to convert old database documents to the new structure automatically.

### Phase 5: AI Resource Structure Upgrade & Validation
